@startuml llm-streaming
' Relaying an SSE stream: where usage arrives, and where fallback stops being available.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/llm/request-handling.md
!include _style.puml

participant "Agent\ncontainer" as agent
participant "LLM Gateway" as gw #90EE90
participant "Upstream\nprovider" as prov #FFE4B5

agent -> gw : streaming LLM request

note over gw
  **Adapter fixups applied before forwarding**
  ....
  **OpenAI:** inject stream_options {"include_usage": true}
  when absent, else no usage is emitted at all. The extra
  terminal chunk has an empty choices array, which client
  libraries tolerate, and is relayed to the agent unchanged.
  ....
  **Vertex:** append ?alt=sse to :streamGenerateContent when
  absent, else Vertex returns a JSON-array stream and the
  SSE relay never engages.
end note

gw -> prov : forward

== Before the first chunk: fallback IS available ==

alt #FFF8DC pre-stream failure
  note over gw, prov : Connection error, timeout before the first\nbyte, or an error response returned before\nstreaming begins.
  gw -> gw : walk the fallback chain
end

prov --> gw : SSE **message_start** (**input_tokens**)
gw --> agent : relay

== First chunk relayed: THE POINT OF NO RETURN ==

loop content chunks (xN)
  prov --> gw : SSE chunk
  gw --> agent : relay immediately\n(no buffering)
end

alt #FFF8DC stream completes
  prov --> gw : **message_delta**\n(**cumulative output_tokens**)
  gw --> agent : relay
  prov --> gw : **message_stop** (carries **no** usage)
  gw --> agent : relay
  gw -> gw : **spend update**, after the\nstream completes
  note over gw
    A stream that ends without usage metadata is
    counted as **zero spend** and logged at warning
    level: acceptable under the soft-guardrail model,
    and the log keeps it visible to operators.
  end note

else mid-stream failure (after the first chunk)
  gw --> agent : close the agent's SSE stream\nwith an error event
  note over gw, prov #FFE4B5
    **No fallback, and no retry.** The agent has already
    received partial output. Replaying the request on
    another provider would produce a different, possibly
    contradictory continuation of what it already read.
  end note
end

note over agent, prov
  **Budget is checked pre-call only** (step 5), against the
  last-known spend state. There is no mid-stream enforcement:
  aborting mid-response would leave the agent with an unusable
  partial answer while the provider still charges for the full
  generation.
end note
@enduml
